	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Requirement_assignment_arm  Entity: Requirement_source  
   <express_ref linkend="requirement_assignment:arm:Requirement_assignment_arm.Requirement_source"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Requirement_assignment_arm.Requirement_source">
A <b>Requirement_source</b> is a relationship between a requirement (via the <express_ref linkend="requirement_view_definition:arm:Requirement_view_definition_arm.Requirement_view_definition"/> entity) and the data types representing the source of the requirement
<example>
The source of the requirement "the vehicle shall have a maximum power output of at least 150BHP" could be a document representing the findings of a
market survey of sports car buyers.
</example>
	</ext_description>
