	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Requirement_assignment_arm  Entity: Satisfies_requirement  
   <express_ref linkend="requirement_assignment:arm:Requirement_assignment_arm.Satisfies_requirement"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Requirement_assignment_arm.Satisfies_requirement">
A <b>Satisfies_requirement</b> is a relationship between an item (specified in <express_ref linkend="requirement_assignment:arm:Requirement_assignment_arm.requirement_satisfaction_item"/>) and a requirement, asserting that the item satisfies the identified requirement.
<example>
A data type used to represent a vehicle's engine with a power output of 160BHP could be asserted to satisfy a requirement "the vehicle shall have a maximum power output of at least 150BHP".
</example>
	</ext_description>
